    "created_at": "2011-05-05T19:34:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-05-05T19:34:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If we want IPython to die at every other error, I can only catch the AliasError.  I don't actually think that's a good idea, but it would conform with current practices of making IPython crash and exit at the first sign of unrecognized trouble.\n\nI think IPython should only crash when something is unrecoverable, not at every possible bug in IPython, but that's something of a separate issue. \n"
  },
